label.value: Albumin Measurement

value.value: A quantitative measurement of albumin present in a sample.

label.value: Alkaline Phosphatase Measurement

value.value: A quantitative measurement of alkaline phosphatase present in a sample.

label.value: Alanine Aminotransferase Measurement

value.value: A quantitative measurement of alanine aminotransferase present in a sample.

label.value: Amylase Measurement

value.value: A quantitative measurement of amylase present in a sample.

label.value: Proband

value.value: The affected family member who seeks medical attention for a genetic disorder thereby bringing the family under study.

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of oropharyngeal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Mediastinal Mixed Nongerminomatous Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: An extragonadal nongerminomatous malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum and is composed of two or more germ cell tumor types.  It manifests with respiratory distress, thoracic pain, cough, superior vena cava syndrome, or hoarseness.

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer with tumor size 2 centimeters or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer with tumor size more than 2 centimeters, but not more than 4 centimeters in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer with tumor size more than 4 centimeters in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer with tumor invading the larynx, deep/extrinsic muscle of tongue, medial pterygoid muscles, hard palate, or mandible. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Oropharyngeal cancer with tumor invading the lateral pterygoid muscle, pterygoid plates, lateral nasopharynx, or skull base or encases carotid artery. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of hypopharyngeal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer with tumor limited to one subsite of the hypopharynx and with tumor size 2 centimeters or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Benign Mediastinal Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: A germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum. There is no evidence of atypia or metastases.

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer with tumor invading more than one subsite of hypopharynx or an adjacent site, or with tumor size more than 2 centimeters, but not more than 4 centimeters in greatest dimension without fixation of the hemilarynx. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer with tumor size more than 4 centimeters in greatest dimension, or with fixation of the hemilarynx. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pT4a TNM Finding V6

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer with tumor invading thyroid/cricoid cartilage, hyoid bone, thyroid gland, esophagus or central compartment soft tissue. (from AJCC 6ht Ed.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Hypopharyngeal cancer with tumor invading prevertebral fascia, encasing carotid artery, or involving mediastinal structures. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of nasopharyngeal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with tumor confined to the nasopharynx. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with tumor extending into the soft tissue. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Malignant Mediastinal Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: An extragonadal malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum.  This category includes seminoma, embryonal carcinoma, yolk sac tumor, choriocarcinoma, mixed germ cell tumors, and immature malignant teratoma.

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pT2a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with tumor extending into the oropharynx and/or nasal cavity without parapharyngeal extension. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pT2b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with parapharyngeal extension. Parapharyngeal extension denotes posterolateral infiltration of tumor beyond the pharyngobasilar fascia. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with tumor involving bony structures and/or paranasal sinuses. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with intracranial extension and /or involvement of cranial nerves, infratemporal fossa, hypopharynx, orbit, or masticator space. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Hypopharyngeal Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of hypopharyngeal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of nasopharyngeal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Oropharyngeal Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of oropharyngeal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Aspartate Aminotransferase Measurement

value.value: A quantitative measurement of aspartate aminotransferase present in a sample.

label.value: Transplant Conditioning

value.value: Administration of high doses of chemotherapy or radiation therapy, as well as immunosuppressive therapy, to a transplant recipient prior to a bone marrow or hematopoietic stem cell transplant.  Conditioning destroys the patient's abnormal blood cells or cancer, as well as slows the patient's immune response against the donor bone marrow (graft rejection).

label.value: Bacterial Count

value.value: The quantitative determination of bacterial populations. The two most widely used methods for determining bacterial numbers are: 1) the standard, or viable, plate count method and 2) spectrophotometric (turbidimetric) analysis.

label.value: Retroperitoneal Germ Cell Tumor
Absolute Basophil Count

value.value: The total number of white blood cells that are basophils. It is calculated by multiplying the white blood cell count by the percent of basophils in the differential white blood cell count.

label.value: Basophil to Leukocyte Ratio

value.value: The determination of the ratio of basophils to leukocytes in a blood sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of nasopharyngeal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with unilateral metastasis to one or more lymph nodes, 6 cm or less in greatest dimension, above the supraclavicular fossa. Midline nodes are considered ipsilateral nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasopharyngeal Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasopharyngeal cancer with bilateral metastasis to one or more lymph nodes, 6 cm or less in greatest dimension, above the supraclavicular fossa. Midline nodes are considered ipsilateral nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)
